:INFO
The Fantasy Trilogy That Taught Me to Love Complicated People
Joe Abercrombie's First Law trilogy opens with three characters who would be \
villains in a more conventional fantasy novel. Logen Ninefingers is a barbarian \
with a history of atrocities. Glokta is a crippled torturer who was once a hero. \
Jezal is a vain and cowardly nobleman. By the end of the first book I cared about \
all three of them. Abercrombie does something most fantasy writers do not attempt: \
he asks what heroism looks like when the people doing it are genuinely flawed.

